org.latency4j.processing

Class Latency4JResourceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.latency4j.processing.Latency4JResourceManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Latency4JResourceManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

    Can be used to manage the handlers and requirements declared within a given Latency4J configuration.

      • getAlertHandler

        public AlertHandler getAlertHandler(java.lang.String id)

        Returns a reference to a stored alert handler with the given id.

        Parameters:
        id - The identifier of the alert handler to retrieve.
        Returns:
        The alert handler with the specified id if the manager holds a reference to it and NULL otherwise.

      • containsRequirement

        public boolean containsRequirement(java.lang.String workCategory)

        Indicates if the manager contains a reference to the latency requirement for the given category.

        Parameters:
        workCategory - The category of the requirement to search for.
        Returns:
        True if this manager contains a requirement for the given category, and False otherwise.
        See Also:
        getLatencyRequirement(String), registerLatencyRequirement(LatencyRequirement)

      • getLatencyRequirement

        public LatencyRequirement getLatencyRequirement(java.lang.String workCategory)

        Returns a reference to the requirement corresponding to the given category where such a requirement had been previously registered with the manager.

        Parameters:
        workCategory - The category of the requirement to search for.
        Returns:
        The requirement for the specified category if one has been registered and Null otherwise.
        See Also:
        registerLatencyRequirement(LatencyRequirement), containsRequirement(String)

      • registerLatencyRequirement

        public void registerLatencyRequirement(LatencyRequirement requirement)

        Stores a reference to the specified requirement in the internal storage map. The stored requirement can be retrieved later using the requirement category.

        Parameters:
        requirement - The requirement to store.
        See Also:
        containsRequirement(String), AsynchronousLatencyMonitorFactory.init()
